  "prompt": "How do I know true love?",
  "response": "Recognizing true love can be subjective, but here are some key indicators:\n\n1. Mutual respect\n- You value each other's opinions and feelings\n- You treat each other with kindness\n- You support each other's goals and dreams\n\n2. Trust and honesty\n- You can be vulnerable with each other\n- You communicate openly\n- There's no need for secrets or deceit\n\n3. Emotional and physical connection\n- You feel comfortable and safe together\n- You enjoy each other's company\n- You have genuine intimacy beyond physical attraction\n\n4. Unconditional acceptance\n- You love each other's strengths and flaws\n- You don't try to change the other person\n- You accept each other as you are\n\n5. Commitment\n- You're willing to work through challenges together\n- You see a future with each other\n- You're dedicated to the relationship\n\n6. Growth and support\n- You encourage each other's personal development\n- You help each other become better individuals\n- You're a team facing life's challenges\n\n7. Selflessness\n- You prioritize each other's happiness\n- You're willing to compromise\n- You make sacrifices for the relationship\n\n8. Deep emotional connection\n- You understand each other deeply\n- You can communicate without words\n- You feel a strong emotional bond\n\nRemember, true love is built over time and requires effort from both partners.",
